Probabilistic Methods, Rule Learning

Explanation: 

The paper describes the Adaptive Simulated Annealing (ASA) algorithm, which is a probabilistic optimization method. The algorithm uses a set of rules to adapt the annealing schedule based on the performance of the current solution. This can be seen as a form of rule learning, where the algorithm learns from its own experience to improve its performance. Therefore, the paper belongs to the sub-categories of Probabilistic Methods and Rule Learning.
